1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,533
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:02,933
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,100
(Episode 25)

4
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,600
I thought you'd left, Team Manager.

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,800
I did, but I came back.

6
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,300
Here, at least eat this while you work.

7
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:20,000
Did you get this for me?

8
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,700
What? No, it's just...

9
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:28,500
I appreciate the thought,
but I don't have time to eat right now.

10
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:33,500
Do you really like it that much?

11
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,600
Yes, I do. Very much.

12
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,300
I really like it, Team Manager.

13
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,700
Sorry for interrupting.

14
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,700
No, it's not like that.

15
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,100
What's not like that? What do you mean?

16
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,500
We weren't talking about anything.

17
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,233
Manager Seo, if you haven't had dinner,
would you like some sushi?

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,400
Team Manager bought it for me.

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,800
No, if it was bought for you,
why would I eat it?

20
00:01:05,033 --> 00:01:06,200
I'm going home.

21
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:08,933
Wait, Manager Seo.

22
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,900
You two finish what you were doing.

23
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,533
No, really! It's not like that!

24
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,000
But what exactly is "not like that?"

25
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,300
What did we even do?

26
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:21,433
Exactly.

27
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,900
Joy, I can finally raise you again.

28
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:30,200
I'm back as your mom!

29
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,933
Let's go to the pantry.

30
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,733
Sushi is all about freshness.

31
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:39,000
I said I don't have time to eat.

32
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,700
Ms. Cho Eun Ae is very bold, right?

33
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,300
Is this fun?

34
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:50,000
What? What is?

35
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,033
You're enjoying this situation,
aren't you?

36
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:55,133
Why would you say something like that?

37
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:59,133
I'm not heartless enough
to enjoy seeing you hurt.

38
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,600
You know that.

39
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,933
How about we play a round of badminton
before heading home?

40
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,600
You idiot.

41
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,500
Me?

42
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:20,000
No, I mean me.

43
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,800
I shouldn't have said
you bought the sushi for me.

44
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,533
- Are you always this dense?
- Sorry?

45
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:31,333
Did my friend Cho Rong say that last time?
That I'm dense?

46
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,700
So you are dense. No wonder.

47
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,933
This is all because of you, Team Manager.

48
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,733
Why bring sushi in the first place?

49
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:43,400
I don't even know what the problem is.

50
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,800
I asked if you liked Joy that much,

51
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,400
and you said you did.

52
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,700
Did you perhaps mean something else
by that?

53
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,600
What do you mean, "something else?"

54
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:58,900
Go ahead and eat.

55
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:01,833
It's really good.

56
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,400
Why do you keep smiling?
Did you swallow air or something?

57
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,133
When did I smile?

58
00:03:13,533 --> 00:03:14,700
Seriously.

59
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,233
The password to my safe
is that child's birthday.

60
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:27,400
That child's birthday.
Who on earth is that child...

61
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,533
Seriously...

62
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:33,333
What are you doing?
Aren't you going to sleep?

63
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,033
Mother didn't come home today, did she?

64
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:41,000
No, she said she's staying overnight
at the hospital.

65
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,033
Really?

66
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:45,533
Crystal, do you happen to know
Gyeol's exact birthday?

67
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,500
How would I remember that exactly?

68
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:51,800
It's the same day
as his dad's death anniversary.

69
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:55,500
Okay. You should go to bed.

70
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,300
Where are you going?

71
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:01,300
I have some documents to check
in the study.

72
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,300
Come back quickly.

73
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:05,100
I can't sleep well
without your arm as a pillow.

74
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:08,233
Okay, I'll be back soon, you silly thing.

75
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:16,000
But why is he asking
about Gyeol's birthday?

76
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:34,633
Hold on.

77
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,133
It has to be...

78
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,000
somewhere in this room.

79
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:45,033
But the master bedroom is shared
with Mother, so...

80
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:47,000
Where could it be?

81
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,633
There was a good spot.

82
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,833
It must be in the study.

83
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,900
In movies,

84
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,500
if you move something like this,
a hidden door should...

85
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,700
It won't open. Wait.

86
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,800
That's it.

87
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,700
Open this...

88
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,400
Found it.

89
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:23,100
Father really watched a lot of movies.

90
00:05:24,033 --> 00:05:25,133
Inside a bookshelf...

91
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,133
Let me see.

92
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:29,100
Press this.

93
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:31,300
- Gyeol's birthday is...
- Please enter...

94
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,733
- Manager Han's death anniversary...
- the password or fingerprint.

95
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,600
This number has not been registered.

96
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,600
Then my birthday?

97
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,533
- Wait, then...
- Please enter the password...

98
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,833
- No.
- This number has not been registered.

99
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:47,833
Min Ho?

100
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,000
This number has not been registered.

101
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,200
This is driving me crazy.

102
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,633
Then when is that child's birthday?

103
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,800
Maybe Children's Day?

104
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,900
You scared me.

105
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:16,700
How long have you been standing there?

106
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,500
I just came in.

107
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:22,400
Really? Me?

108
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:26,500
I was just looking for something
to take to your grandpa's hospital room.

109
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:30,733
Did you just come back from the hospital?

110
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,800
Yes.

111
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,933
All right, go upstairs and rest.

112
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:38,800
Okay. Good night.

113
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,500
Okay.

114
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,200
My heart nearly stopped.

115
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,733
Wait, who on earth is that child?

116
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,633
I tried every family member's birthday,
and nothing worked. So what...

117
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,400
I'm home.

118
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:59,400
Why did you come home so late?

119
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,800
I dropped Manager Seo off,
and there was traffic.

120
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,700
Is now really the time to be worrying
about driving her home?

121
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:07,333
If you had time for that,
you should've gone to see Grandpa.

122
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,700
I'll manage my time on my own.
Get some rest.

123
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,133
Why is he so confident?

124
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,600
Who on earth is that child?

125
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Come in.

126
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:32,333
I actually have something to say.

127
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,400
- Sure, sit down.
- Okay.

128
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,300
Looks like you started the design.

129
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,700
No, I'm just sketching a rough draft.

130
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:44,100
You know our team outsourced
to Lucas Architecture, right?

131
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:47,100
Really? That's good. They're very skilled.

132
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,933
That's not the main point, is it?

133
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:55,000
What's going on with you and Ms. Cho?
Are you two dating?

134
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,600
What are you talking about? No, we're not.

135
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:00,100
Then what was that situation
I saw earlier?

136
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,200
It looked like a passionate confession
from her.

137
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,933
Do I really need to answer that?

138
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,933
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

139
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:12,400
But if anything changes
between you and her,

140
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,300
at least be clear with Seung Ri.

141
00:08:18,233 --> 00:08:21,200
I can't watch her suffer for long.

142
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,333
So be clear about your feelings.

143
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:26,700
Only then can she give up.

144
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:29,400
Min Ho,
I already made my feelings clear...

145
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,600
a long time ago.

146
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,300
I can't control
how the other person takes it.

147
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:37,100
That's true.

148
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,733
I'm honestly jealous.

149
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,700
Think it over carefully.
You and Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

150
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:49,833
Get some rest.

151
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,400
Tell me.

152
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:02,800
Where is your arrow pointing right now?

153
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,800
Do you really like it that much?

154
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,133
Yes, I do. Very much.

155
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,933
I really like it, Team Manager.

156
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,100
Hey, Seo Seung Ri.

157
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,200
Mom!

158
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,900
- What?
- Seo Seung Ri has finally gone crazy.

159
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:47,300
What?

160
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:51,000
I'm telling you, she's gone crazy.
She's out of her mind.

161
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,033
Come over here, hurry.

162
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:53,700
- Let go of me!
- Come here, quickly!

163
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,600
- Let go!
- Seriously.

164
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,900
That hurts. Hey.

165
00:09:58,933 --> 00:10:00,733
- You're late.
- Dad!

166
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,600
Come here.

167
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,200
Why that little...

168
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:15,000
See? She's not being normal.

169
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,400
Seung Ri...

170
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,000
It must be because of Gyeol, right?

171
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,600
What?

172
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,500
You know that
when Seung Ri starts dancing like that,

173
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,033
it means she's really struggling.

174
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,433
The last time I saw that
was ten years ago,

175
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:50,100
when Gyeol went to study abroad
right after his discharge.

176
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:54,800
Why is she so hung up on Gyeol...

177
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:57,200
when Min Ho is crazy about her?

178
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,000
I have to go to the hospital
early tomorrow morning.

179
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,000
What's the point of going so early...

180
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,100
to a place where you're treated
like an outsider...

181
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,733
no matter how much you devote yourself?

182
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:27,100
Is that you, Eun Ae?
Try to come home earlier.

183
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:30,100
Yes, good night.

184
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,133
Patient transfer complete.
Move to the operating room.

185
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:44,000
Propofol, 70. Rocuronium, 50.
Airway secured.

186
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:46,100
Begin incision. Scalpel.

187
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,000
Heavy bleeding. Suction.

188
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,133
- Cho Eun Nim.
- Blood pressure dropping. Pressin.

189
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,900
- Cho Eun Nim.
- Blood pressure up to 85.

190
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,100
Eun Ae.

191
00:11:57,700 --> 00:12:00,400
Another consultation
for some writer you barely know?

192
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,433
Yeah, it's a consultation.

193
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,700
Be honest. This is your novel, right?

194
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,633
Let's see.
The author's name is Doro Dorothy.

195
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:11,200
You like Dorothy from The Wizard of Oz,
so that's your pen name, right?

196
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,900
What are you talking about?

197
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,100
Even if I'm dense, I still have instincts.

198
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:21,500
I should've realized
when I kept hearing typing at night.

199
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,400
Fine, it's my web novel.

200
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:28,433
Do you even have time for that?
You have exams...

201
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,433
I dropped out.

202
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:33,300
Dropped out? Hey, Cho Eun Nim!

203
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,100
Are you crazy?

204
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:38,400
When? When did you drop out?

205
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:40,000
About a year ago.

206
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,100
Then you dropped out a year ago...

207
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:44,800
and have been writing web novels
since then?

208
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,800
Yeah.

209
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,733
I'm doing pretty well these days.

210
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:50,800
My novel is in the Top Ten,
and the income...

211
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,600
Top Ten? Income?
That's not the issue right now!

212
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:56,600
How could you make such a huge decision...

213
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,500
without even discussing it
with our parents?

214
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,100
Aren't you curious why I made that choice?

215
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,600
Fine, tell me. What is it?

216
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:05,900
Why did you have to make...

217
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,333
such a drastic decision?

218
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:11,200
Forget it. Even if you knew,
what would change?

219
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,933
If there was no other choice,
you should've at least tried to explain...

220
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:17,500
and made an effort to persuade them.

221
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,933
And you've been taking allowance
and tuition money from Dad all this time.

222
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:26,200
Do you even know how he earns that money?

223
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:28,733
I didn't touch a single penny.
I saved it all.

224
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,633
I'll pay it back later.

225
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:32,733
That's not the point.

226
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,700
Can you leave?

227
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:38,000
I have to upload this
by tomorrow morning.

228
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:39,900
Is that really what matters right now?

229
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,700
You... Seriously.

230
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,400
Joy, what do I do?

231
00:13:59,033 --> 00:14:00,700
Eun Nim dropped out of medical school.

232
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:05,133
Even Mom's last hope has been shattered.

233
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:08,700
Hope means the desire
for something to happen...

234
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:11,800
or the possibility that things
will go well in the future.

235
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,400
Why you...

236
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:17,000
Did this happen
because I haven't been taking care of you?

237
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:22,800
Joy,
can you tell me if returning to school...

238
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,333
or readmission is possible
after dropping out?

239
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
(Haedeul Hospital)

240
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,800
Did you sleep well, Chairman, Madam?

241
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,333
Welcome, Mr. Seo.

242
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,300
You didn't have to come so early.
I'm right here.

243
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,100
Yeong Hwa,

244
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:54,033
could you go to the café
on the first floor and get us some coffee?

245
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,133
Mr. Seo likes coffee.

246
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,000
Okay. Take your time talking.

247
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,633
I'll take a walk while I'm at it.

248
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:06,600
Madam, don't forget
you have a health checkup this afternoon.

249
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:09,633
I had one last year,
so they said I don't need one this year.

250
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:11,100
What are you talking about?

251
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:13,733
You can never be too sure
about your health.

252
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:15,400
Can't you tell just by looking at me?

253
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,533
You must really be feeling better,

254
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:20,700
seeing how you're nagging again.

255
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:22,500
I'll be back.

256
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,500
What's the urgent report?

257
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,500
Yes, Chairman.

258
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,800
In the past,
overseas adoption agencies' records...

259
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,533
weren't properly digitized,
so we couldn't get them,

260
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,400
but they were recently updated.

261
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,933
These are the children
among overseas adoptees from that time...

262
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:46,100
whose region, age, and other details
almost match.

263
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,000
Maybe seeing them will jog your memory.

264
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:58,333
Looking at them like this,
I really can't tell.

265
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:04,300
Did you confirm if any of them had
a large burn scar on the leg?

266
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:08,400
It was too long ago,
so the records aren't that detailed.

267
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:11,900
I see.

268
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:19,133
These eyes...

269
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,433
Don't you think
this one looks a little like her?

270
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:25,800
I'm not sure. Now that you mention it,

271
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,400
maybe a little.

272
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:32,300
Father.

273
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:34,900
Did you sleep well?

274
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:40,033
Why come twice a day?
You're busy with work.

275
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:44,133
I'll wait outside.

276
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,400
What photos were you looking at?

277
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,500
They looked pretty old at a glance.

278
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,333
You don't need to know.

279
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:59,433
Are Min Ho
and Gyeol's competition preparations...

280
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,500
going smoothly?

281
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,100
Yes, of course.

282
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:06,533
Min Ho seems to be deep
into the design process already.

283
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:08,100
What about Gyeol?

284
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:11,200
Sorry? Gyeol?

285
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,900
Well, with Gyeol...

286
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:16,733
It's hard to tell
if he's working hard or not,

287
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:20,600
so there hasn't been
any particular report yet.

288
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:24,800
Keep this in mind.
Fair management and supervision.

289
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,033
You're in this race too, CEO Ko.

290
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,000
Of course.

291
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:33,400
When do you plan
to fill the executive assistant position?

292
00:17:33,733 --> 00:17:35,500
I'll finalize it soon.

293
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,700
I've already told Seong Jun what I think.

294
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:41,700
Make sure everything follows
the proper order.

295
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:44,633
Don't force anything.

296
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,533
Yes, of course.

297
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,300
Right.

298
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:51,200
Dr. Kim said
you might be discharged tomorrow.

299
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:54,200
I want to leave right now,

300
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:58,533
but no one at the hospital listens to me.

301
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:00,200
But Father,

302
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,600
since you're already hospitalized,

303
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,200
why don't you seriously start treatment...

304
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,400
Not that again.

305
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,533
Hey, Father says to go in.

306
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:29,800
What are those photos?

307
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:31,833
I'll go in.

308
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,700
Do my words mean nothing to you?

309
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,333
Have a good day.

310
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,400
What are you doing?

311
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,933
Did you sleep well, Mom?

312
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:24,933
What are you two doing?

313
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:28,500
Dad and I started doing five minutes
of morning meditation every day.

314
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Meditation?

315
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,500
Meditation plays a wonderful role
in emptying what has built up inside me...

316
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,033
and filling me with something new.

317
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:37,800
It helps cut off useless attachments...

318
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:40,800
Dad, I'm going to be late. I'll wash up.

319
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,700
Okay, while I get breakfast ready,

320
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:44,133
- finish getting ready for kindergarten.
- Okay.

321
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,833
I'm thinking of going
to Mother's place today.

322
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:51,400
Why? You finally have a day off.
Get some rest.

323
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:54,733
We should tell Mother
about your appointment too.

324
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,033
About that...

325
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:00,400
How about we tell her
when I get my first paycheck?

326
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,900
- Why?
- Well...

327
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:06,400
We've put her through
so many ups and downs.

328
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:10,200
I don't want her to lose the peace
she's finally found.

329
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:14,000
But which school is it?

330
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,700
Bit Na will be late.
I need to hurry with breakfast.

331
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,333
Look at the time.

332
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,200
Could it be far away?

333
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,333
I'm fine with seeing him only on weekends.

334
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,100
(Kangsu Construction)

335
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:36,900
Hey, Eun Hyeong.

336
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:40,633
Advice? About what?

337
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:45,400
All right. Come by the office
around the time I get off work...

338
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,700
and call me.

339
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,333
Are you busy, Dad?

340
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:54,333
What? I guess so. Why?

341
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:57,033
Actually, I need some advice.

342
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,800
- You too?
- What?

343
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,600
Your brother just called
saying he needed advice,

344
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,500
so I told him to come to the office.

345
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,833
Perfect timing.

346
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,533
I was thinking this is something
that requires a family meeting.

347
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,400
Why? Did something happen at work?

348
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,900
No, it's not about me.

349
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,600
I have something to do right now,
so I'll see you later with Eun Hyeong.

350
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:19,400
What is going on now?

351
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:20,900
Dad.

352
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:23,300
This has to stay a secret from Mom, okay?

353
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:26,900
It's something
your mom can't know about again?

354
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:28,800
Yes. It'll be a disaster if she finds out.

355
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,700
It's been simmered down really well.

356
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,900
Everyone seems low on energy these days,

357
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,700
so I should help them recover like this.

358
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:50,600
Goodness.

359
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,433
If you're that worried,

360
00:21:53,633 --> 00:21:56,100
why don't you go apologize first, Grandma?

361
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:57,500
Tell her you misspoke without knowing.

362
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:00,833
It's not that simple, you brat.

363
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,833
I upset someone...

364
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:06,900
who cares so deeply about her family.

365
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:12,800
What's this?
What brings you all the way here, Yeon Ja?

366
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,900
What do you mean? You're right across.

367
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:18,100
Cho Rong, here.

368
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:19,700
What is this?

369
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,300
I simmered some oxtail.

370
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:24,833
Everyone seems drained lately.

371
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,900
Why bring it to us too?

372
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:31,000
You made it for your family.

373
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,133
Aren't you and Cho Rong family too?

374
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,433
Yeon Ja,

375
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,400
- I'm sorry.
- What?

376
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,100
I almost turned someone dear
into a stranger...

377
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,500
just because of one wrong spelling.

378
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:55,900
Strictly speaking,
you got the meaning wrong.

379
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,500
Philosophy and fortune-telling.

380
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:59,900
Whether it was the spelling
or the meaning,

381
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:03,400
I was wrong.

382
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,700
Forget it.

383
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:09,600
I was narrow-minded too
because I had a lot bottled up.

384
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:14,300
That's refreshing. I feel much better now.

385
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,933
By the way, Yeon Ja,

386
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:19,933
aren't you going to that line dance thing
these days?

387
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:21,933
I'm thinking of slowly going back.

388
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:41,200
- Good work, everyone.
- Good work.

389
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,500
- Good work.
- Good work.

390
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:47,300
Good work, everyone.
Looks like she hasn't been around lately.

391
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:49,400
She? Who?

392
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:51,333
Ms. Kang Yeon Ja?

393
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:53,933
Right. Why hasn't she been coming lately?

394
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,833
Maybe she realized her limits...

395
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:57,400
or finally learned her place.

396
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:00,400
Then I'll see you next time.

397
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:02,033
- Good work.
- Good work.

398
00:24:02,033 --> 00:24:03,733
- Good work.
- Good work.

399
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:06,800
Yes!

400
00:24:10,733 --> 00:24:13,300
I think I should call her.

401
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:17,100
What? You're calling the real estate lady?

402
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:23,700
Hello,
I'm in the same line dance class as you.

403
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:26,033
Yes, you remember me.

404
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:29,133
I was wondering
why you haven't been coming lately.

405
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:32,200
From the next class?

406
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,500
Great, then I'll see you next time.

407
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,900
Since when have you been so nosy?

408
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:43,933
What? Can't classmates call each other?

409
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,433
Is she doing that on purpose or what?

410
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:49,133
She wants to see me get annoyed?

411
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:52,233
Hey! Wait for me.

412
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:56,100
Finally done.

413
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:05,400
When my novel gets an update,
Napkin Genius is usually first...

414
00:25:07,500 --> 00:25:08,500
I must be crazy.

415
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:11,700
Why did I bring up that perverted psycho?

416
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:22,500
(Eun Ae)

417
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:27,800
What is it, Eun Ae?

418
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:30,400
To your office?

419
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:34,433
What? Dad and Eun Hyeong too?

420
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:37,433
You want to keep this huge thing
a secret from the whole family forever?

421
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:40,733
Fine, I'll see you later.

422
00:25:45,233 --> 00:25:47,500
Since it's come to this,

423
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:49,433
I'll face it head-on.

424
00:25:51,933 --> 00:25:53,600
Still, I should avoid Mom for now.

425
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:56,900
When did Eun Nim leave?

426
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,200
I wanted to feed her rice
with beef bone soup.

427
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:05,733
Dr. Cho, are you at the library?

428
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:11,233
Okay, study hard.

429
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:19,500
It's Mom.
Can you come outside for a moment?

430
00:26:19,733 --> 00:26:21,300
Outside? Outside where?

431
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,500
I'm in front of your school library.

432
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,800
I packed you lunch.

433
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:27,500
Mom, I'm in ER practice right now.

434
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:28,500
I'm busy, so I'm hanging up.

435
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,700
Why ER practice all of a sudden?

436
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,733
If she's in practice, I can't go in.

437
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,533
Hello, ma'am.

438
00:26:48,100 --> 00:26:51,933
Hye Ji,
why haven't you been coming over lately?

439
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:55,400
I'm busy preparing for the national exam.

440
00:26:55,833 --> 00:26:58,800
Right, none of you have time
to hang out these days.

441
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:01,533
But why aren't you at ER practice?

442
00:27:01,700 --> 00:27:02,700
Sorry?

443
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,833
Eun Ae, we've got an emergency.
Mom is at my school right now...

444
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:08,233
Dad?

445
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:11,733
Eun Nim.

446
00:27:12,900 --> 00:27:15,000
- What are you doing here?
- What?

447
00:27:16,533 --> 00:27:18,633
Well, I...

448
00:27:20,233 --> 00:27:21,600
Dad, we're in trouble.

449
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:25,000
Trouble? What trouble?

450
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:28,500
Eun Nim said
she's in ER practice right now.

451
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,433
Are you in different practice groups?

452
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:34,300
You don't know yet...

453
00:27:36,900 --> 00:27:37,900
What?

454
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:41,800
What don't I know?

455
00:27:45,633 --> 00:27:46,633
Tell me, Hye Ji.

456
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:49,433
Now.

457
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,300
Actually, Eun Nim...

458
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:54,800
Eun Nim...

459
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:56,500
What?

460
00:27:59,233 --> 00:28:01,800
What did you just say?

461
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:04,733
Eun Nim...

462
00:28:07,333 --> 00:28:08,333
- She dropped out?
- You dropped out?

463
00:28:12,433 --> 00:28:15,200
(Our Happy Days)

464
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:16,600
She'll find out anyway,

465
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:18,500
so I'm going to tell Mom everything today.

466
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:21,033
Was I the only one who didn't know again?
Just me?

467
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:22,200
Today is the only chance.

468
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:22,900
It's gone.

469
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:24,600
It was definitely here.

470
00:28:24,933 --> 00:28:25,800
You scared me.

471
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:27,033
"Sweet dreams?"

472
00:28:27,733 --> 00:28:30,200
What is this? "Dream of me?"

473
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:31,900
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
